# Privacy Policy for SAT Mock Test

**Last Updated: October 5, 2024**

## Introduction

SAT Mock Test ("we," "our," or "us") is committed to protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and safeguard your information when you use our free mobile application.

## Information We Collect

### No Personal Information Collection
SAT Mock Test is designed to be completely private. We do not collect, store, or transmit any personal information including:
- Names, email addresses, or contact information
- Device identifiers or unique IDs
- Location data
- Usage analytics or tracking data
- Any other personally identifiable information

### Local Data Storage Only
The app stores data locally on your device only:
- Quiz progress and scores (stored locally using SharedPreferences)
- User preferences and settings
- No data is transmitted to external servers

## How We Use Information

Since we do not collect personal information, we do not use, share, or sell any personal data. All app functionality operates entirely on your device.

## Data Security

- All data remains on your device
- No data transmission occurs
- No third-party analytics or tracking
- No advertising networks or data brokers

## Third-Party Services

### Minimal Third-Party Integration
Our app uses only essential third-party services:

1. **URL Launcher**: Used only for the "Rate Us" feature to open app store pages
   - No data collection or tracking
   - Opens external app store URLs only when user requests

2. **Math Rendering**: Local mathematical equation rendering
   - No data transmission
   - Processes equations locally on device

## Children's Privacy

SAT Mock Test is designed for educational use and may be used by students under 13. Since we do not collect any personal information, we comply with all children's privacy regulations including COPPA (Children's Online Privacy Protection Act).

## Data Retention

- No personal data is retained by us
- Local app data remains on your device until you uninstall the app
- You can clear all app data by uninstalling and reinstalling the app

## Your Rights

Since we do not collect personal information, traditional data subject rights (access, deletion, portability) do not apply. However, you have complete control over your local data:

- Delete all app data by uninstalling the app
- Clear app cache through device settings
- No data to request, modify, or delete from our servers

## App Permissions

SAT Mock Test requests minimal permissions:

- **Internet Access**: Only for "Rate Us" feature to open app store pages
- **Storage**: Local storage for app data and preferences
- No camera, microphone, contacts, or location permissions required

## Updates to This Policy

We may update this Privacy Policy occasionally. Changes will be posted on this page with an updated "Last Updated" date. Continued use of the app after changes constitutes acceptance of the new policy.

## Contact Information

If you have questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at:

- **Email**: icebergcrypto786@gmail.com
- **App Store**: Through the app's "Rate Us" feature

## Compliance

This Privacy Policy complies with:
- General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR)
- California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA)
- Children's Online Privacy Protection Act (COPPA)
- Google Play Store requirements
- App Store requirements

## Free App Disclaimer

SAT Mock Test is provided completely free of charge with no hidden costs, subscriptions, or premium features. We do not monetize user data because we do not collect any.

## Educational Use

This app is designed for educational purposes to help students prepare for the SAT exam. All content is for practice purposes only and does not guarantee actual SAT performance.

## Data Minimization

We follow the principle of data minimization - we collect no data because our app functions entirely offline and locally.

---

**By using SAT Mock Test, you agree to this Privacy Policy. If you do not agree, please do not use the app.**

**This policy is effective as of the date listed above and applies to all users of the SAT Mock Test application.**
